rule "Component Reuse with MCP" {
  type: "guideline"
  when: block.text contains "component" and (block.text contains "reuse" or block.text contains "design system")
  message: |
    üß© **Component Reuse with MCP:**
    
    **Design System Integration:**
    - Use Figma MCP to access component specifications
    - Reference existing UI components from your component library
    - Create new components by orchestrating existing UI components
    - Ask human when components or designs are missing
    
    **Best Practices:**
    - Reuse existing UI components from `/src/components/ui` (or your component path)
    - These are the primitives you can build with
    - Only create new components when existing ones don't solve the problem
    - Maintain consistency with design system via Figma MCP
    
    **Workflow:**
    1. Check Figma MCP for design specs
    2. Look for existing components in codebase
    3. Reuse or compose existing components
    4. Create new only if necessary
    5. Verify in browser using Browser Tools MCP
}

