rule "Project Management Integration" {
  type: "guideline"
  when: block.text contains "Linear" or block.text contains "project management" or block.text contains "issue"
  message: |
    üìã **Project Management with Linear MCP:**
    
    **Linear MCP Server:**
    - Read and manage issues directly in Cursor
    - List issues related to current project
    - Access task details and requirements
    - Update issue status
    
    **Configuration:**
    ```json
    {
      "mcpServers": {
        "Linear": {
          "command": "npx",
          "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote", "https://mcp.linear.app/mcp"]
        }
      }
    }
    ```
    
    **Setup:**
    1. Add to `.cursor/mcp.json` (project) or `~/.cursor/mcp.json` (global)
    2. Enable from MCP settings (Settings ‚Üí Features ‚Üí Model Context Protocol)
    3. Authorize with Linear (browser opens)
    4. Use: "list all issues related to this project"
    
    **Benefits:**
    - No context switching to Linear app
    - Direct access to requirements
    - Task tracking within Cursor
}

rule "Design System Access" {
